. However, doing that might lead to complications, especially under Native Image. I’m pondering if it’s worth the effort or if I should keep it simple and direct.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reviewing mock maker options**\\n\\nI'm looking at the public API default mock maker, which seems to handle proxies well. For the first test, using an explicit mock maker looks effective. There’s line 613 that seems sufficient, but line 230 is raising some questions. I’m wondering if we can trigger it through the public API with the default plugin. If not, I could set a system property to ensure the initialization error isn't null. However, there’s a possibility that previous tests might have already loaded the class. It’s my first time using InlineDelegate in this context.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_UD1zg475oq6oMSZJRxVuP8cN|fc_009c32a7d957afb9016a21cf4a43e08195ae822d59be18c082", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/InlineDelegateByteBuddyMockMakerTest.java", "limit": 180}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/InlineDelegateByteBuddyMockMakerTest.java\",\"limit\":180}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1333, "output": 738, "cacheRead": 45056, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 47127, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780600620791, "responseId": "resp_009c32a7d957afb9016a21cf2df7f081958ed88bdcdfa17854"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_UD1zg475oq6oMSZJRxVuP8cN|fc_009c32a7d957afb9016a21cf4a43e08195ae822d59be18c082", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_mockito.mockito_core;\n\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.mockito.MockMakers;\nimport org.mockito.MockedConstruction;\nimport org.mockito.Mockito;\n\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicReference;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\nimport static org.mockito.Mockito.withSettings;\n\npublic class InlineDelegateByteBuddyMockMakerTest {\n    static {\n        System.setProperty(\"net.bytebuddy.experimental\", \"true\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void inlineMockMakerCreatesFinalClassMockUsingConstructors() throws Exception {\n        exerciseInlineMockito(\n                () -> {\n                    final FinalGreetingService service =\n                            Mockito.mock(\n                                    FinalGreetingService.class,\n                                    withSettings().mockMaker(MockMakers.INLINE));\n\n                    Mockito.when(service.greeting(\"Mockito\")).thenReturn(\"Hello Mockito\");\n\n                    assertThat(Mockito.mockingDetails(service).isMock()).isTrue();\n                    assertThat(service.getClass()).isEqualTo(FinalGreetingService.class);\n                    assertThat(service.greeting(\"Mockito\")).isEqualTo(\"Hello Mockito\");\n                });\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void inlineMockMakerMocksConstructionThroughPublicApi() throws Exception {\n        exerciseInlineMockito(\n                () -> {\n                    final AtomicReference<MockedConstruction.Context> constructionContext =\n                            new AtomicReference<>();\n                    try (MockedConstruction<ConstructedGreetingService> mockedConstruction =\n                            Mockito.mockConstruction(\n                                    ConstructedGreetingService.class,\n                                    withSettings().mockMaker(MockMakers.INLINE),\n                                    (mock, context) -> {\n                                        constructionContext.set(context);\n                                        Mockito.when(mock.greeting())\n                                                .thenReturn(\"constructed mock\");\n                                    })) {\n                        final ConstructedGreetingService service =\n                                new ConstructedGreetingService(\"real\", 7);\n\n                        assertThat(service.greeting()).isEqualTo(\"constructed mock\");\n                        assertThat(mockedConstruction.constructed()).containsExactly(service);\n                    }\n\n                    final MockedConstruction.Context context = constructionContext.get();\n                    assertThat(context).isNotNull();\n                    assertThat(context.arguments()).hasSize(2);\n                    assertThat(context.arguments().get(0)).isEqualTo(\"real\");\n                    assertThat(context.arguments().get(1)).isEqualTo(7);\n                    assertThat(context.constructor().getParameterTypes())\n                            .containsExactly(String.class, int.class);\n                });\n    }\n\n    private static void exerciseInlineMockito(ThrowingRunnable exercise) throws Exception {\n        try {\n            exercise.run();\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        } catch (Exception exception) {\n            final Error unsupportedFeatureError = findUnsupportedFeatureError(exception);\n            if (unsupportedFeatureError == null) {\n                throw exception;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static Error findUnsupportedFeatureError(Throwable throwable) {\n        Throwable current = throwable;\n        while (current != null) {\n            if (current instanceof Error\n                    && NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError((Error) current)) {\n                return (Error) current;\n            }\n            current = current.getCause();\n        }\n        return null;\n    }\n\n    @FunctionalInterface\n    private interface ThrowingRunnable {\n        void run() throws Exception;\n    }\n\n    public static final class FinalGreetingService {\n        private final String prefix;\n\n        public FinalGreetingService(\n                String prefix, int retryCount, boolean enabled, Object dependency) {\n            this.prefix = prefix + retryCount + enabled + dependency;\n        }\n\n        public final String greeting(String name) {\n            return prefix + name;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class ConstructedGreetingService {\n        private final String prefix;\n        private final int retryCount;\n\n        public ConstructedGreetingService(String prefix, int retryCount) {\n            this.prefix = prefix;\n            this.retryCount = retryCount;\n        }\n\n        public String greeting() {\n            return prefix + retryCount;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1780600650874}]}
